{
  "updated_summary": "The video begins with a yellow background and lightbulb, transitioning to a fitness montage with push-ups, planks, and core workouts, set to upbeat electronic music and featuring playful animations like an animated pirate ship. A male narrator (Male Voice), speaking in Chinese, introduces the plank as a superior full-body exercise for endurance, clarifying \"not that kind of plank,\" and promising variations. A woman in a white t-shirt and black leggings demonstrates a classic plank on a green yoga mat against a colorful geometric wall, maintaining a straight body line as the narrator instructs viewers to lie face down, supporting the upper body on hands and lower body on tiptoes, with palms under shoulders, reinforced by on-screen Chinese text like '保持雙臂伸直' and '不要抬起脖子', and visual cues. The narrator (Male Voice) emphasizes proper form, instructing to hold the plank for 30 seconds, indicated by on-screen text '30秒' and '完美!', while an animated human muscle diagram highlights core, abs, and back muscles strengthened by the exercise. On-screen text overlays '-45秒', '-1分鐘', '-2分鐘' as the narrator (Male Voice) encourages increasing hold times, followed by a grid of six animated plank variations. A muscular man in blue shorts then demonstrates a forearm plank, accompanied by yellow text '15秒全身運動', as the narrator (Male Voice) encourages viewers to upgrade their routine. The video concludes with a purple gradient screen displaying '#1 俯臥平板撐' and a progress bar, transitioning back to the animated muscle diagram, as the narrator (Male Voice) introduces the "prone plank" as the first exercise, training the core and biceps."
}
